                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City policeman</hi>, 10). I produce a certificate—(<hi rend="italic">Read: "Central Criminal Court—<persName id="t18551022-name-537">
                        <interp inst="t18551022-name-537" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18551022-name-537" type="surname" value="COLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18551022-name-537" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>Charles Coley</persName>; Convicted April</hi>, 1851, <hi rend="italic">of stealing a purse and money from the person, having then been before convicted—Trans<lb></lb>ported for Seven Years</hi>")—I was present at the trial—the prisoner is the person.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
GUILTY</hi>. Aged 21.—<hi rend="italic">
